                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Dutch translation by <persName>Isaac Titsingh</persName> of two
                            Japanese herbals; <title>Qua ji of versameling van Planten en gewassen
                                Bloemen en Kruyden</title>, translated from the Japanese work
                                <title>Kai</title> written by <persName xml:lang="ja" source="IANA"
                                >島田 充房</persName> | <persName xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA"
                                >Shimada, Mitsufusa</persName> and <persName xml:lang="ja"
                                source="IANA">小野 蘭山</persName> | <persName xml:lang="ja-Latn"
                                source="IANA">Ono, Ranzan</persName>, and <title>Japanse Naamen van
                                de in Japan groeyende Boomen, struyken, heesters, planten en
                                kruijden</title>. There are additional titles given which describe
                            both translated works; on the spine of the binding, <title>Exposé du
                                Livre des Fleurs Traduit du Japonais en Hollandais
                                P.M.Titzing</title>, and on the manuscript itself, <title>Kwaji of
                                Kruydboek</title>. </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="nl" source="IANA">Dutch</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_59_1">

                            <author key="person_73860738" source="VIAF">
                                <persName>Isaac Titsingh</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title type="main" xml:lang="nl" source="IANA">Qua ji of versameling van
                                Planten en gewassen Bloemen en Kruyden</title>

                            <filiation><p>The first published translation of Kai was by L.Savatier,
                                    Botanique japonaise. Livres Kwa-wi traduit du japonais avec
                                    l’aide de M.Saba (Paris, 1875). See MS 9008; The Phillipps
                                    manuscripts: catalogus librorum manuscriptum in bibliotheca
                                    D.Thomae Phillipps, Bt. (London: Holland Press, 1968),
                                    p.142.</p></filiation>
                        </msItem>

